    <paperBody>
        <page n="01" image="va.au.ss.1857.03.11.01">
            <div type="l">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>For the Spectator; Abolition</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>W. B. B.; Elendale, Va.</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Examination of Abolition: what might the effect be of an abolition decreee;
                    impossibility of two races living equally side by side; looks at the Bible, the
                    Greeks &amp; Romans for examples. Some sections are faint, blurry, hard to
                    read.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>The Great Snow Storm; Interesting Facts</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Excerpts from National Observatory Report on the 1/18/57 snowstorm. It
                    stretched from North Carolina to New England. Calls for a system of weather
                    reporting via telegraph.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1857.03.11.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The President's Address</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Review of Buchanan's inaugural address. Issues include Squatter
                    Sovereignty, the Tariff, Public Lands, Highway to the Pacific.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Reforms in Congress</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complains about the disorderly proceedings of the end of the last session.
                    Makes the process impossible to follow, inefficient. Calls for the removal of
                    desks from the halls, to cut down on the length of speeches, abolition of the
                    franking privilege.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>A New Paper</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Annoucnment that a new paper is being published in Richmond, called "The
                    South."</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>For the Spectator; To Will Woffle ??</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Kate Kareless</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Top is illegible, but must be part of continuing debate over women's
                    ability to run the town.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Important Decsision</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>The gist of the decision is that both the Wilmot Proviso and Squatter
                    Sovereignty are unconstitutional. It is an opinion we have always held...we hope
                    the question will be regarded as definately and finally settled.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report on the Dred Scott Decision, delivered 3/7/57. Details the main
                    points, agrees with it.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Many Citizens</trailer>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Walker</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <pf>Maj.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Letter nominating Walker to run for House of Delegates. Hopes the rousing
                    local support will encourage him to run.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report of a recent ball in Monteray.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>The Inauguration</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report on the Inauguration including the text of Buchanan's
                speech.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="o">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>Died</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Argenbright</ln>
                        <pf>John</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Died from an explosion of a gun, age 17 on 3/5/57</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="o">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>Died</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hayne?</ln>
                        <pf>Adam</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Sipe</ln>
                        <pf>Julia A.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Julia Sipe, on 3/5/57.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Lots of news from Washington about the Senate, the Cabinet. Print at top of
                page is so faint it is barely readable. Congressional report, Markets in
            7.</pageNote>
